article.description: — Majesty Brandon came off the bench to tally 17 points to lead Canisius to an 89-70 win over Quinnipiac on Saturday.
article.headline: Brandon scores 17 to lead Canisius over Quinnipiac 89-70
article.linkText: Brandon scores 17 to lead Canisius over Quinnipiac 89-70
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- — Majesty Brandon came off the bench to tally 17 points to lead Canisius to an 89-70 win over Quinnipiac on Saturday. Jordan Henderson had 13 points and eight rebounds for Canisius (5-3, 5-3 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), which earned its fourth straight win. Jacco Fritz also scored 13 points. Malek Green had seven rebounds. Savion Lewis had 15 points for the Bobcats (5-9, 3-7). The Golden Griffins improve to 2-0 against the Bobcats this season. Canisius defeated Quinnipiac 74-67 on Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
